ess while recommending greater emphasis on industry-oriented content, practical and project-based learning, emerging technologies, internships, skill development, improved infrastructure, and stronger industry-academia interaction to enhance students'' employability and holistic development.","feedbackAnalysis":"Feedback was collected from parents, students, faculty members, and academic peers regarding the curriculum and learning environment. Overall, stakeholders appreciated the relevance of the curriculum and teaching-learning process while recommending greater emphasis on industry-oriented content, practical and project-based learning, emerging technologies, internships, skill development, improved infrastructure, and stronger industry-academia interaction to enhance students'' employability and holistic development.","actionTakenReport":"Based on the stakeholder feedback, the department strengthened industry-institute interaction through industrial visits, expert lectures, internships, and MoUs with industries. Project-based learning, mini-projects, and value-added certification courses were encouraged, while practical components, case studies, and emerging technologies were integrated into course delivery. The institute also upgraded laboratory facilities, library resources, and digital infrastructure to provide a better learning environment and support continuous curriculum improvement.","foreignCollaborations":"2","nationalCollaborations":"6","functionalMousCount":"12","__auditSignOff":{"submittedBy":{"name":"Dr Anupama Patil","designation":"Director","role":"director","date":"2026-07-11T04:42:37.663Z"}}}', '{"studentStrength":[{"Sr No":"1","Class":"F.Y Mechanical Engineering","No. of Student":"118","Total":"118"},{"Sr No":"2","Class":"S.Y Mechanical Engineering","No. of Student":"106","Total":"106"},{"Sr No":"3","Class":"T.Y Mechanical Engineering","No. of Student":"24","Total":"24"},{"Sr No":"4","Class":"F.Y Semiconductor Engineering","No. of Student":"76"