llowing stakeholders: Alumni, Academic Peers, Faculty Members, Students, Parents, and Employers.\\nThe folder includes:\\n1. Sample feedback forms collected from each stakeholder group.\\n2. Feedback Analysis Reports and Action Taken Reports (ATRs) based on the feedback received.","feedbackAnalysis":"Stakeholder Feedback Analysis Folder Link: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1MkDXTuTEsrZ5R7VosWEqBdwlKv34_QlF?usp=drive_link\\nThis folder contains feedback-related documents for the following stakeholders: Alumni, Academic Peers, Faculty Members, Students, Parents, and Employers.\\nThe folder includes:\\n1. Sample feedback forms collected from each stakeholder group.\\n2. Feedback Analysis Reports and Action Taken Reports (ATRs) based on the feedback received.","actionTakenReport":"Stakeholder Feedback Analysis Folder Link: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1MkDXTuTEsrZ5R7VosWEqBdwlKv34_QlF?usp=drive_link\\nThis folder contains feedback-related documents for the following stakeholders: Alumni, Academic Peers, Faculty Members, Students, Parents, and Employers.\\nThe folder includes:\\n1. Sample feedback forms collected from each stakeholder group.\\n2. Feedback Analysis Reports and Action Taken Reports (ATRs) based on the feedback received.","foreignCollaborations":"The School has consistently promoted research through publications in reputed\\ninternational journals during the academic years 2025–2026. Faculty members have\\npublished more than 40 research papers in internationally recognized journals and\\npublishers, including Nature Scientific Reports, Springer, IEEE, Elsevier (Science\\nDirect), Wiley, World Scientific, Frontiers in Artificial Intelligence, AI, and\\nComputational Biology and Chemistry. Several publications are co-authored with\\nresearchers from other institutions, reflecting collaborative research practices and\\ninterdisciplinary engagement. The research covers emerging areas such as Artificial\\nIntelligence, Machine Learning, Cyber Security, Internet of Things (IoT), Renewable\\nEnergy, Medical Image Processing, Smart Agriculture, Wireless Communication, and\\nApplied Mathematics.\\nExp: School of Engineering, Swinburne University of Technology, Hawthorn, Australia\\nhttps://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-025-22310-w","nationalCollaborations":"The School has established active research collaborations with several national\\ninstitutions through joint research publications and conference proceedings during the\\nacademic years 2025–2026. Faculty members have collaborated with researchers from\\nreputed Indian universities, engineering colleges, research organizations, and industry\\npartners, These collaborative research efforts span interdisciplinary domains such as\\nArtificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Cyber Security, Internet of Things (IoT),\\nRenewable Energy, Healthcare, Wireless Communication, and Applied Mathematics.\\nThe collaborations have strengthened the institution&#39;s research ecosystem, promoted\\nknowledge sharing, enhanced publication quality, and facilitated interdisciplinary\\nresearch at the national level.\\nExp: VIT, Vellore, Symbiosis International (Deemed University)\\nhttps://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11299572\\nhttps://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-025-04591-3","functionalMousCount":"4","__auditSignOff":{"submittedBy":{"name":"Dr Rahul Sharma","designation":"Director","role":"director","date":"2026-07-11T11:14:22.509Z"}}}', '{"studentStrength":[{"Sr No":"1","Class":"FY B.Tech CSE","No. of Student":"1275","Total":"2840"},{"Sr No":"2","Class":"SY B.Tech CSE","No. of Student":"702","Total":"2840"},{"Sr No":"3","Class":"TY B.Tech CSE","No. of Student":"494","Total":"2840"},{"Sr No":"4","Class":"FIY B.Tech CSE","No. of Student":"369","Total":"2840"},{"Sr No":"5","Class":"FY BCA","No. of Student":"98","Total":"272"},{"Sr No":"6","Class":"SY BCA","No. of Student":"62","Total":"272"},{"Sr No":"7","Class":"TY BCA","No. of Student":"112","Total":"272"},{"Sr No":"8"